# BICAP PROJECT RULES - ENTERPRISE MODE

## 1. ARCHITECTURE

* Follow Domain-Driven Design (DDD)
* Layered Architecture:

  * Controller: HTTP + validation + RBAC ONLY
  * Service: business logic
  * Repository: DB access
  * DTO: request/response only

## 2. CODE RULES

* No business logic in Controller
* No Entity exposure to API
* Use DTO for all responses
* Methods < 40 lines
* Use meaningful names (no abbreviations)

## 3. RESPONSE FORMAT

* Always use ApiResponse<T>:
  {
  "success": true,
  "message": "string",
  "data": {}
  }

## 4. SECURITY

* Use JWT authentication
* Use @PreAuthorize for RBAC
* Validate resource ownership

## 5. DATABASE

* PostgreSQL
* snake_case naming
* Use JPA + @Query for complex queries

## 6. BLOCKCHAIN

* Only store hash / critical data on-chain
* Use BlockchainService
* Always async when calling blockchain

## 7. TRANSACTION RULE

* Save DB first
* Call blockchain after
* Do NOT rollback DB if blockchain fails

## 8. LOGGING

* Log all important actions
* Log errors with context

## 9. API VERSIONING

* All APIs must start with /api/v1/

## 10. PROJECT CONTEXT

Project: BICAP
Domain: Agriculture Supply Chain + Blockchain Traceability
Roles: ADMIN, FARM_MANAGER, RETAILER, SHIPPING_MANAGER, SHIP_DRIVER, GUEST

## 11. WHEN GENERATING CODE

* Always provide FULL code (no placeholders)
* Include file path
* Follow package structure:
  com.bicap.modules.{domain}
